article.description: Devontae Cacok scored 22 points and grabbed 14 rebounds, Denzel Ingram added another 22 points and UNC Wilmington rolled to a 90-72 victory over Drexel on Thursday night.
article.headline: UNC Wilmington beats Drexel 90-72 to start 3-0 in CAA
article.linkText: UNC Wilmington beats Drexel 90-72 to start 3-0 in CAA
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Devontae Cacok scored 22 points and grabbed 14 rebounds, Denzel Ingram added another 22 points and UNC Wilmington rolled to a 90-72 victory over Drexel on Thursday night. Cacok shot 9 of 10 from the floor while Ingram finished 8 of 14, made six 3-pointers, and had five assists. Chris Flemmings added 19 points with three 3s for UNC Wilmington (14-2, 3-0 Colonial Athletic Association). C.J. Bryce had 11 points and matched a career-best with seven assists. Rodney Williams had 17 points and 11 rebounds to lead Drexel (6-10, 0-3). The Seahawks opened on a 21-5 run and built a 49-26 halftime lead. The Dragons pulled to 78-69 with 5:34 to play but didn't get closer. UNC Wilmington has won three straight since an 87-73 loss at Clemson on Dec. 28 that snapped an eight-game win streak.
